def add_columns(df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:
    df['percent_score'] = df['student_score'] / df['max_score']

    df['course_started'] = 0
    df.loc[df['lessons_completed'] >= 1, 'course_started'] = 1

    df['course_100'] = 0
    df.loc[df['lessons_completed'] == df['course_lesson_cnt'], 'course_100'] = 1

    return df
inner = add_columns(inner)
outer = add_columns(outer)

def unique_cnt_plot(df: pd.DataFrame, x: str, y: str, 
                    title=None, xlabel=None, ylabel=None,
                    orient='v', order='count', palette = LETOVO_PALETTE):
  if orient == 'v':
    data = df.groupby(x)[y].nunique()
  if orient == 'h':
    data = df.groupby(y)[x].nunique()

  if order == 'count':
    ordnung = data.sort_values(ascending=False).index
  if order == 'index':
    ordnung = data.sort_index().index
  
  data = data.reset_index()
  ax = sns.barplot(data=data, x=x, y=y, 
                   errorbar=('ci', 0), order=ordnung, palette=palette)
  ax.bar_label(ax.containers[0])
  ax.set(title=title, xlabel=xlabel, ylabel=ylabel)
  return ax

def funnel(df, fig, name, step_names, course_fin_type='100_percent'):
    user_cnt = df['lo_id'].nunique()
    users_start = df[df['course_started'] == 1]['lo_id'].nunique()
    if course_fin_type == '100_percent':
        users_fin = df[df['course_100'] == 1]['lo_id'].nunique()
    if course_fin_type == 'finalist':
        users_fin = df[df['tick_status'] == 'accepted']['lo_id'].nunique()

    names = step_names
    values = [user_cnt, users_start, users_fin]

    fig.add_trace(go.Funnel(
        name = name,
        y = names,
        x = values,
        orientation='h',
        textinfo = "value+percent previous",
        textfont={'size':16}
    )
    )

def make_funnels_subject(df, step_names=['', '', '']):    
    subjects = df['subject_name'].unique()

    for sub in subjects:
        fig = go.Figure()

        data = df[df['subject_name'] == sub]

        courses = data['course_name'].unique()

        for course in courses:
            funnel(data[data['course_name'] == course], fig, course, step_names)
        if len(courses) > 1:
            fig.update_layout(title=sub)
        else:
            fig.update_layout(title=sub + ", " + course)
        fig.show()
    
    return

make_funnels_subject(inner)

def continuous_by_groups_plot(df: pd.DataFrame, x: str, y: str, outliers=False,
                              title: str=None, xlabel: str=None, ylabel: str=None, palette='Set2',
                              hue: str=None, hue_legend_labels: str=None, hue_legend_title: str=None):

  #  ,    - 
  df = df.drop_duplicates(subset=['lo_id', 'course_id'])
  group = df.groupby(y)[x]
  #
  order = group.median().sort_values(ascending=False).index
  ax = sns.boxplot(data=df, x=x, y=y, showfliers=outliers, hue=hue, 
                   palette=palette, order=order,
                   medianprops={'linewidth':'2', 'color':'white'})
  if title:
    ax.set_title(title)
  if xlabel:
    ax.set_xlabel(xlabel)
  if ylabel:
    ax.set_ylabel(ylabel)
  if hue_legend_labels:
    handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
    labels = hue_legend_labels
    ax.legend(handles, labels, title=hue_legend_title)
  ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(ticker.PercentFormatter(1, decimals=0))

  display(group.describe().mul(100).round(2).sort_values(by='50%', ascending=False))
  return ax
